This '''[[Courier droid/Legends|courier droid]]''' was [[Torture/Legends|tortured]] under the supervision of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] [[Droid/Legends|droid]] supervisor [[EV-9D9/Legends|EV-9D9]].<ref name="RotJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref>

The silver droid screamed in pain as a [[traction-test bed]] pulled their right arm off.<ref name="ABFTTofE" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:New_Aquisitions_ROTJ.png|thumb|200px|left|[[CZ-series_communications/business_droid|CZ-series]] droid near the doorway of the torture chamber.]] Note that this droid is rather similar to [[2-1B/Legends|2-1B]] in shape and often gets the [[fanon]] name 2-1A. This name has never been confirmed. The droid is sometimes confused with the "interpreter droid" that Jabba "became angry with", along with a [[CZ-series secretary/comm droid|CZ-series communications/business droid]], that was later replaced by [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]]. In the game ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'', they can be seen alone in the torture chamber with a leg almost torn off. Their vocabulator is not the same as the one on a [[2-1B surgical droid/Legends|2-1B surgical droid]].

